               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; incipit of Text I; directives to the ministers and their abbreviations; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
On the incipit page of Text I (fols. 3r), a few lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Text I is called Mäṣḥafä ṭǝmqät in Additio 1 (fol. 36v).</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="coloph1">
                     <colophon>
                        <locus target="36v"/>Fol. 36v, l. 4: ተፈጸመ፡ መጽሐፈ፡ ጥምቀት፡ በሰላመ፡ እግዚአብሔር፡ አሜን። ዛቲ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ዘቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ እንባ፡ ሐረሳ፡ ዘአድ፡ ሕያው፡ በዘመኑ፡ ዘአጽሐፋ፡ ቀሲስ፡ ፍሥሐ፡ ጊዮርጊስ። ወገበዙሂ [lac.] ከማሁ፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ስሞሙ፡ ኀበ፡ ዓምደ፡ ወርቅ፡ በቀለመ፡ ጽድቅ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ ወጸሐፈሁኒ፡ ኃጥእ፡ ዘድንግል።<foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                        <note>The colophon states that the Ms. was owned by the church Däbrä Mikaʾel ʾƎnba Ḥarisay (Mikaʾel ʿAd Ḥǝyaw). It mentions also the commissioner, Fǝśśǝḥa Giyorgis, and the scribe, Zä-Dǝngǝl.</note>
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
